        "creation_date": 1292414376,
        "answer_count": 8,
        "title": "Apostrophe doesn&#39;t get translated properly when placed in a resource bundle",
        "body": "<p>Apostrophe doesn't get translated properly when placed in a resource bundle.<\/p>\n\n<pre><code>key = {0}'s brush is {1} centimeters tall\n\n(e.g. Sam's brush is 4 centimeters tall)\n<\/code><\/pre>\n\n<p>The apostrophe gets missed if I format the above key from a <code>java.util.ResourceBundle<\/code> What could be the problem here?<\/p>\n",
        "question_id": 4449639,
        "tags": [
            "java",
            "resourcebundle"
        ],
        "score": 105,
        "accepted_answer_id": 4449668,
        "is_answered": true,
        "view_count": 44828
    },
    "question_comments": [{
        "owner": {
            "profile_image": "https://i.sstatic.net/SwKRE.png?s=256",
            "account_id": 1129042,
            "user_type": "registered",
            "user_id": 1115554,
            "link": "https://stackoverflow.com/users/1115554/micha",
            "reputation": 49842,
            "display_name": "micha",
            "accept_rate": 100
        },
        "content_license": "CC BY-SA 3.0",
        "score": 5,
        "post_id": 4449639,
        "edited": false,
        "creation_date": 1380907815,
        "comment_id": 28388785
    }],
    "answers": [
        {
            "owner": {
                "profile_image": "https://www.gravatar.com/avatar/211ea8bb93bbd3df4eca1d59fe2c7e0d?s=256&d=identicon&r=PG",
                "account_id": 93007,
                "user_type": "registered",
                "user_id": 254643,
                "link": "https://stackoverflow.com/users/254643/raghuram",
                "reputation": 52833,
                "display_name": "Raghuram"
            },
            "content_license": "CC BY-SA 2.5",
            "score": 149,
            "is_accepted": true,
            "last_activity_date": 1292414551,
            "creation_date": 1292414551,
            "body": "<p>You should escape the single quote as <\/p>\n\n<pre><code>key = {0}''s brush is {1} centimeters tall\n<\/code><\/pre>\n",
            "answer_id": 4449668,
            "question_id": 4449639
        },
        {
            "owner": {
                "profile_image": "https://i.sstatic.net/oTmxxFgA.jpg?s=256",
                "account_id": 104911,
                "user_type": "registered",
                "user_id": 280244,
                "link": "https://stackoverflow.com/users/280244/ralph",
                "reputation": 121291,
                "display_name": "Ralph",
                "accept_rate": 81
            },
            "content_license": "CC BY-SA 2.5",
            "score": 37,
            "is_accepted": false,
            "last_activity_date": 1292414563,
            "creation_date": 1292414563,
            "body": "<p>I strongly belive that the problem is not the ressource bundle but the <a href=\"http://download.oracle.com/javase/6/docs/api/java/text/MessageFormat.html\" rel=\"noreferrer\">MessageFormater<\/a> you use to print the message:<\/p>\n\n<p><a href=\"http://download.oracle.com/javase/6/docs/api/java/text/MessageFormat.html\" rel=\"noreferrer\">From MessageFormater java doc<\/a>:<\/p>\n\n<blockquote>\n  <p>Within a String, '' (<em>two single quotes<\/em> ) represents a\n  single quote. A QuotedString can\n  contain arbitrary characters except\n  single quotes; the surrounding single\n  quotes are removed. An UnquotedString\n  can contain arbitrary characters\n  except single quotes and left curly\n  brackets. Thus, a string that should\n  result in the formatted message\n  '{0}' can be written as '''{'0}''\n  or '''{0}'''.<\/p>\n<\/blockquote>\n\n<p>So you need to write:<\/p>\n\n<pre><code>{0}''s brush is {1} centimeters tall\n<\/code><\/pre>\n",
            "answer_id": 4449670,
            "question_id": 4449639
        },
        {
            "owner": {
                "profile_image": "https://www.gravatar.com/avatar/ab0dbfe30b420c583435282cff5ba4b4?s=256&d=identicon&r=PG&f=y&so-version=2",
                "account_id": 1131752,
                "user_type": "registered",
                "user_id": 1117679,
                "link": "https://stackoverflow.com/users/1117679/sorrymissjackson",
                "reputation": 2725,
                "display_name": "sorrymissjackson"
            },
            "content_license": "CC BY-SA 3.0",
            "score": 9,
            "is_accepted": false,
            "last_activity_date": 1454398327,
            "creation_date": 1454398327,
            "body": "<p>Adding to @Ralph's answer:\nYou will realize that this is a <code>MessageFormat<\/code> thing when you have a text like<\/p>\n\n<pre><code>text1=It's too late\n<\/code><\/pre>\n\n<p>versus<\/p>\n\n<pre><code>text2={0}''s too late\n<\/code><\/pre>\n\n<p><code>text1<\/code> would probably not run through a MessageFormater (e.g. spring has different code paths if arguments are passed or not), whereas <code>text2<\/code> would.\nSo if you used two single quotes in <code>text1<\/code>, they may / will display as such. So you'll need to check if any arguments get formatted in or not and use one or two single quotes accordingly.<\/p>\n",
            "answer_id": 35147502,
            "question_id": 4449639
        },
        {
            "owner": {
                "profile_image": "https://i.sstatic.net/5W9TK.jpg?s=256",
                "account_id": 43539,
                "user_type": "registered",
                "user_id": 127320,
                "link": "https://stackoverflow.com/users/127320/aravind-yarram",
                "reputation": 80467,
                "display_name": "Aravind Yarram",
                "accept_rate": 87
            },
            "content_license": "CC BY-SA 3.0",
            "score": 7,
            "is_accepted": false,
            "last_activity_date": 1484302016,
            "creation_date": 1292414680,
            "body": "<p>Look at the <a href=\"http://docs.oracle.com/javase/8/docs/api/java/text/MessageFormat.html\" rel=\"nofollow noreferrer\">javadoc here<\/a><\/p>\n\n<blockquote>\n  <p>Within a String, \"''\" represents a\n  single quote. A QuotedString can\n  contain arbitrary characters except\n  single quotes; the surrounding single\n  quotes are removed. An UnquotedString\n  can contain arbitrary characters\n  except single quotes and left curly\n  brackets. Thus, a string that should\n  result in the formatted message\n  \"'{0}'\" can be written as \"'''{'0}''\"\n  or \"'''{0}'''\".<\/p>\n<\/blockquote>\n",
            "answer_id": 4449689,
            "question_id": 4449639,
            "last_edit_date": 1484302016
        },
        {
            "owner": {
                "profile_image": "https://www.gravatar.com/avatar/6d4702638a002d554210df405b61e194?s=256&d=identicon&r=PG&f=y&so-version=2",
                "account_id": 7619751,
                "user_type": "registered",
                "user_id": 5778099,
                "link": "https://stackoverflow.com/users/5778099/nestor-milyaev",
                "reputation": 6733,
                "display_name": "Nestor Milyaev",
                "accept_rate": 53
            },
            "content_license": "CC BY-SA 3.0",
            "score": 7,
            "is_accepted": false,
            "last_activity_date": 1466784017,
            "creation_date": 1466784017,
            "body": "<p>If you are completely stuck, as I was (none of the above worked), you can replace the apostrophe sign with its Unicode: \\u0027. Remember you are always allowed to use UTF symbol in your properties file.<\/p>\n",
            "answer_id": 38017558,
            "question_id": 4449639
        },
        {
            "owner": {
                "profile_image": "https://www.gravatar.com/avatar/76de515c95df423e53b72d35b882f0f5?s=256&d=identicon&r=PG",
                "account_id": 255965,
                "user_type": "registered",
                "user_id": 536358,
                "link": "https://stackoverflow.com/users/536358/samuel-parsonage",
                "reputation": 3127,
                "display_name": "Samuel Parsonage",
                "accept_rate": 38
            },
            "content_license": "CC BY-SA 2.5",
            "score": 5,
            "is_accepted": false,
            "last_activity_date": 1292414590,
            "creation_date": 1292414590,
            "body": "<p>You need to double single quote i.e. {0}''s brush is {1} centimeters tall<\/p>\n",
            "answer_id": 4449675,
            "question_id": 4449639
        },
        {
            "owner": {
                "profile_image": "https://www.gravatar.com/avatar/6427a973b7cf06c775284c8fd816e12b?s=256&d=identicon&r=PG&f=y&so-version=2",
                "account_id": 253331,
